results.name: The Euler phi function values of the powerful numbers, A000010(A001694(n)).
comment: The sum of the reciprocals of all the terms of this sequence is Murata's constant Product_{p prime}(1 + 1/(p-1)^2) (A065485).
Sequence is injective: no value occurs more than once. - _Amiram Eldar_ and _Antti Karttunen_, Sep 30 2019
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
Eckford Cohen, A property of Dedekind's psi-function, Proceedings of the American Mathematical Society, Vol. 12, No. 6 (1961), p. 996.
mathematica: EulerPhi /@ Join[{1}, Select[Range@ 1200, Min@ FactorInteger[#][[All, 2]] > 1 &]] (* after _Harvey P. Dale_ at A001694 *)
program: (PARI) lista(nn) = apply(x->eulerphi(x), select(x->ispowerful(x), vector(nn, k, k))); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Jan 11 2019
results.author: _Amiram Eldar_, Jan 11 2019
